üìå Executive Summary

In this lab, I investigated a simulated insider-threat incident where a single user account was suspected of causing significant disruption within an organization. Initial indicators suggested misuse of company resources and potential credential exposure through public code repositories.

The objective of this investigation was to:

Identify exposed credentials and sensitive data

Trace the insider‚Äôs digital footprint

Analyze malicious tooling used

Correlate OSINT findings to assess risk and intent

The investigation leveraged OSINT techniques, GitHub repository analysis, and artifact inspection to reconstruct the attacker‚Äôs actions and assess the impact.

üéØ Investigation Objectives

Identify exposed API keys and credentials

Determine misuse of public repositories

Detect cryptomining activity

Correlate online accounts using OSINT

Attribute actions to a single insider account

üß∞ Tools & Techniques Used

GitHub repository analysis

Commit history review

Base64 decoding

OSINT investigation

Sherlock (username enumeration)

